events.name: Google Design Sprint
events.description:
​Design sprint is a methodology​ used by Google​ for ​creating and testing product​s​ in short time.​ It's a way of finding a solution to a problem effectively, with minimal time and cost.​Various Google products emerged​,​ or got updated​,​ using this process, example: Google Glass, Project Loon, Hangouts and ​much ​more.​

What happens at Design Sprint?


​Participants are broken down into groups. You can come with your own group, team or co-workers. ​​You'll learn how to work as a team and individually to find the best solution to a problem. By the end of the workshop you'll have a functioning prototype. 

Requirements


The session is ​free and ​open to everyone​.
There will be no coding at the session​.​No need to bring anything, just your brain!

​More

This process is used at Google-X​You can apply this methodology to your existing company or startup.

​Register via: http://www.droidcon.ae/?page_id=539​

events.name: Google Golang Workshop!
events.description:
Reserve your seat by filling this registration form

Golang Workshop given by Francesc Campoy; Google Developer Advocate from San Francisco.

Dear GDGers, 

Join us in our event on the 25th of February on Golang; Go is an open source programming language developed by Google. Go makes it easy to build simple, reliable, and efficient software. 

Go compiles quickly to machine code yet has the convenience of garbage collection and the power of run-time reflection. It's a fast, statically typed, compiled language that feels like a dynamically typed, interpreted language. 

About The Speaker

Francesc Campoy Flores is a Developer Advocate for Go and the Cloud at Google. He joined the Go team in 2012 and since then he has written some considerable didactic resources and traveled the world attending conferences, organizing live courses, and meeting fellow gophers. He joined Google in 2011 as a backend software engineer working mostly in C++ and Python, but it was with Go that he rediscovered how fun programming can be. You can find him on twitter as @francesc.

Agenda

07:00pm Welcoming Message 

07:15pm Introduction to Go 

08:00pm - Building your app from scratch 

                  - Advanced topics 

Requirements

- Get your laptops! We're Gonna code! 

- Knowledge in any programming language 

- Download Go 

https://golang.org

events.name: Predictive Churn Analytics using H20 and IBM DSX

venue.name: in5 Innovation Hub
venue.address_1: Boutique Villa #7, Dubai Knowledge Village, Dubai : Location: http://www.in5.ae/#contact

events.description:
Dear all, 

Join us for the next GDG Dubai at In5 (Knowledge village),  we will introduce H20.ai and IBM Data Science Experience trough a predictive churn analytics story telling. 

• H2O is open-source software for big-data analysis. It is produced by the company H2O.ai (formerly 0xdata), which launched in 2011 in Silicon Valley. H2O allows users to fit thousands of potential models as part of discovering patterns in data. H2O's mathematical core is developed with the leadership of Arno Candel, part of Fortune's 2014 "Big Data All Stars". The firm's scientific advisors are experts on statistical learning theory and mathematical optimization. https://www.h2o.ai/

Speaker: Vinod Iyengar is the Director of Business Development and Partnerships at H2O.ai. Vinod comes with over 7 years of marketing and data science experience in multiple startups. He was the founding employee for his previous startup, Activehours, where he helped build the product and bootstrap the user acquisition with growth hacking. He has seen the user base for his companies grow from scratch to millions of customers. He’s built models to score leads, reduce churn, increase conversion, prevent fraud and many more use cases. 

• IBM Data Science Experience is an environment that has everything a data scientist needs to be successful. The Experience is an interactive, collaborative, cloud-based environment where data scientists can use multiple tools to activate their insights. Data scientists can use the best of open source, tap into IBM's unique features, grow their capabilities, and share their successes. https://datascience.ibm.com/

events.name: Time to get hands-on - Cloud Study Jam

venue.name: Google Office, 2nd Floor, Building 9, Canon Building

events.description:
In collaboration with the Cloud Emirates GDG, we are bringing the Cloud Study Jam (w/ Google Certification)!

What is Cloud Study Jam about?
--------------------------------------------
Learn the fundamentals of the Google Cloud Platform, how to run containers on it and how to use the platform for data engineering.

What you will learn:
---------------------------
- Learn how to set up development and production environments in the Cloud.
- Learn how Docker and Kubernetes work, or learn how to process Big Data in the Cloud.
- Get access to Qwiklabs, a Google training tool, free of charge (a $70+ value).
- Get Google-hosted badges for your online profile, to show potential employers what you know about Cloud computing.
- Pave a path towards getting Google Cloud Certification

How long does it take?
--------------------------------
One in-person session of 3 hours, followed by 2-8 hours of self-study.
Agenda:
6:00pm: Three Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs
7:30pm: Break
8:00pm: Intro to Docker or Scientific Data Processing lab
9:00pm: Event ends

*** Remember to bring your laptop ***
Bring a laptop (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.

You will learn how you setup multiple lanes for beta and production deployments and how fastlane integrates into your team communication and product management tools.

About the speaker:
Jan Kettner / Careem
I wanted to be a writer because I did not want to work. But since I did not want to work I did not succeed as a writer. So I became a developer instead, because being lazy can be a good trait for a developer. Most of my career I have been working in Mobile Development. The question what defines good code and how to build good software drives me and any pointers are welcome.

events.name: Build a Google Assistant: Case Study from UAQ Economic Development

venue.name: Google HQ Dubai
venue.address_1: Google Master Card Building - Dubai Internet City building 4 - 3rd Floor

events.description:
• What we'll do
During the meet-up we will present our journey on building a Google Assistant App for the Government:
Google Assistant Introduction
Voice Strategy
Voice UI
Develop a conversation agent using DialogFlow.
Develop a fulfillment application using Google Actions API.
Deploy a Google Assistant Application.

Speakers:

Ndjido Ardo Bar - Google Developer Expert Machine Learning:

Ndjido Ardo BAR is a Lead Data Science at Davidson UAE and is at the moment working in a project related to the Dubai Smart City project.

Ndjido earned a Master Degree in Applied Mathematics at Gaston Berger University in Senegal. His strong background in Maths is coupled with an excellent programming skill in languages like C/C++, Scala, Python. Ndjido loves functional programming and has the chance to use language like Scala to deliver most of Data Science project he is involved in.

He has 7 years experience doing Data Science project, starting at Pasteur Institut as a researcher in BioStatistics. Around 2011 he co-founded a startup specialised in real-time agriculture online market (MLouma). In late 2012, Ndjido joined BearingPoint a French consulting company as a Data Scientist in its Machine Learning team named Hypercube. He was in charge of different activities: developing Algorithms, training customers in Data Science, delivering Machine Learning modelling to different customers. In late 2015, Ndjido joined AXA France as a Data Scientist and delivered a Credit Scoring Model build from customer-centric data and financial KPIs using a Deep Belief Network and a Gradient boosting model.

Ndjido is not only passionated by Maths and AI, he is also an open source activist and love to speak in meetups and conferences what he has learnt from hours and hours of reading and practicing. It's a way for him to give back to community.

Baghdad Gherras - Google Developer Expert Product Design:

Baghdad GHERRAS is a Data Product Manager and Practice Head - Data Science and Machine Learning for a French Consulting Company based in Dubai. He built the first Data Science Consulting team in UAE and worked with private companies as well as government institutions.

He is currently serving as Engagement Manager for Road and Transport Authority in Dubai where he is building Data Science Capabilities. His recent accomplishments include the creation of an Artificial Intelligence Excellence Center and the design of Data Products for Dubai Smart City. He is passionate about the intersection of Machine Learning, Design Thinking and UX Design.

Baghdad is also an Adjunct Professor in Smart Cities at IE University in the MSc Global Business Analytics and Big Data. He is a Google Cloud Developer Lead, member of the Singularity University Dubai Chapter and Organizer of the UAE Data Science Meet-up Group.

He studied Applied Economy at the Business & Management School of Lyon (France), Strategy at the IMBA Lingnan-MIT Sloan (Guangzhou, China), Financial Engineering at the University of Lyon (France) and Data Science via Coursera and the Ecole Polytechnique Summer School.

events.name: Microservices Architecture​
events.description:
In this presentation, Vijay would like to share his experience around MicroServices Architecture.

On a high level, he plans to cover the practical reasoning behind employing and implementing MicroServices Architecture.

Presentation outline :

1. The rationale behind employing microservices architecture Vs monolith
2. Real-world use case
3. Config Server
4. API Gateway
5. Eureka Service Discovery
6. Ribbon Client-side load balancer
7. Hystrix Circuit break pattern fault tolerance
9. Sleuth centralized logging and tracing
10. Inter microservices interaction
11. Drawbacks of microservices architecture

Location: Dubizzle, 10th Floor, Landmark Towers, Dubai Marina.
Near Tram station: Marina Towers

Flutter with Native Android App

Most of the native developer will be hesitant to migrate from native Android to flutter though it has benefits like multi platform. So it will good start to learn how to add flutter to our existing android application.

With this approach architecture will remain same but will use flutter based UI components. These component can be added in both Android and ios project using Dart.
